foreFrameRelayModule.contactinfo: Postal: FORE Systems Inc. 1000 FORE Drive Warrendale, PA 15086-7502 Tel: +1 724 742 6900 Email: nm_mibs@fore.com Web: http://www.fore.com
foreFrameRelayModule.description: This MIB is considered as being required in addition to the standard mibs RFC1604 and RFC1315. It provides configuration and statistics information at frame relay service and connection level.

frextDlcmiTable.name: frextDlcmiTable
frextDlcmiTable.description: The Parameters for the Data Link Connection Management Interface corresponding to any given ifEntry. These parameters are logical extensions to those in contained within the object frDlcmiTable in RFC1315.

frextDlcmiEntry.name: frextDlcmiEntry
frextDlcmiEntry.description: The Parameters for the Data Link Connection Management Interface.

frextDlcmiServiceIfIndex.name: frextDlcmiServiceIfIndex
frextDlcmiServiceIfIndex.description: The Service/FR-UNI identifier ifIndex value of the corresponding ifEntry.

frextDlcmiProfileLmiIndex.name: frextDlcmiProfileLmiIndex
frextDlcmiProfileLmiIndex.description: Index for the LMI profile for this FR service.

frextDlcmiProfileServiceIndex.name: frextDlcmiProfileServiceIndex
frextDlcmiProfileServiceIndex.description: Index of the Service profile for this FR service.

frextDlcmiStatsMonitor.name: frextDlcmiStatsMonitor
frextDlcmiStatsMonitor.description: This object specifies whether statistics are to be counted at a service level, this includes service and connection statistics. When the state changes from enabled to disabled all the related statistics will be frozen at their current value. When the state changes from disabled to enabled then all related statistics will be reset (zeroised). Note that this Monitor is overriden by the netmod level nmFramStatsMonitor. Refer to fore-fram.mib for more details.

frextDlcmiStatsEnabledTimeStamp.name: frextDlcmiStatsEnabledTimeStamp
frextDlcmiStatsEnabledTimeStamp.description: This object reflects the point in time, with reference to sysUpTime, either when frextDlcmiStatsMonitor is set to enabled or when nmFramStatsMonitor is set to enabled. The time will reflect the last StatsMonitor to be enabled. The timestamp provides a starting timestamp for the current statistics that are being counted.

frextDlcmiLmiDlci.name: frextDlcmiLmiDlci
frextDlcmiLmiDlci.description: the dlci upon which LMI traffic will be broadcast. If Q933-AnnexA=0, otherwise STRATACOM=1023.

frextDlcmiLmiFlowControl.name: frextDlcmiLmiFlowControl
frextDlcmiLmiFlowControl.description: Specifies whether STRATACOM LMI based (R-bit) notification performs flow control for the Circuits on this interface.

frextDlcmiRAControl.name: frextDlcmiRAControl
frextDlcmiRAControl.description: Specifies whether Rate Adaptation-RA performs flow control for the Circuits on this interface.

frextDlcmiLmiBandwidthControl.name: frextDlcmiLmiBandwidthControl
frextDlcmiLmiBandwidthControl.description: Specifies whether STRATACOM LMI based CIR notification affects the CIR flow control parameters for the connections on this interface.

frextDlcmiRxAbortedFrames.name: frextDlcmiRxAbortedFrames
frextDlcmiRxAbortedFrames.description: The number of aborted frames received on this Frame Relay logical interface.A frame is considered aborted after receiving 7 or more continuous ones.

frextDlcmiRcvCrcErrors.name: frextDlcmiRcvCrcErrors
frextDlcmiRcvCrcErrors.description: Specifies the number of frames receive with CRC errors on this interface.

frextDlcmiRcvShortFrames.name: frextDlcmiRcvShortFrames
frextDlcmiRcvShortFrames.description: The number of frames containing less than 5 octets received on this interface.

frextDlcmiRcvLongFrames.name: frextDlcmiRcvLongFrames
frextDlcmiRcvLongFrames.description: The number of frames containing greater than 8191 octets received on this interface.

frextDlcmiRcvInvalidDLCI.name: frextDlcmiRcvInvalidDLCI
frextDlcmiRcvInvalidDLCI.description: The number of frames with an invalid DLCI received on this interface.

frextDlcmiRcvUnknownErrs.name: frextDlcmiRcvUnknownErrs
frextDlcmiRcvUnknownErrs.description: The number of frames with other errors received on this interface.

frextDlcmiLmiTxStatusResponses.name: frextDlcmiLmiTxStatusResponses
frextDlcmiLmiTxStatusResponses.description: Number of STATUS messages transmited on this interface.

frextDlcmiLmiTxFullStatusResponses.name: frextDlcmiLmiTxFullStatusResponses
frextDlcmiLmiTxFullStatusResponses.description: Number of STATUS messages with full status IE transmited on this interface.

frextDlcmiLmiTxFullStatusEnquiries.name: frextDlcmiLmiTxFullStatusEnquiries
frextDlcmiLmiTxFullStatusEnquiries.description: Number of STATUS ENQUIRY messages with full status IE transmited on this interface.

frextDlcmiLmiRxStatusResponses.name: frextDlcmiLmiRxStatusResponses
frextDlcmiLmiRxStatusResponses.description: Number of STATUS messages received on this interface.

frextDlcmiLmiRxFullStatusResponses.name: frextDlcmiLmiRxFullStatusResponses
frextDlcmiLmiRxFullStatusResponses.description: Number of STATUS messages with full status IE received on this interface.

frextDlcmiLmiRxStatusEnquiries.name: frextDlcmiLmiRxStatusEnquiries
frextDlcmiLmiRxStatusEnquiries.description: Number of STATUS messages received on this interface.

frextDlcmiLmiRxFullStatusEnquiries.name: frextDlcmiLmiRxFullStatusEnquiries
frextDlcmiLmiRxFullStatusEnquiries.description: Number of STATUS ENQUIRY messages with full status IE (Information Element) receive on this interface.

frextDlcmiLmiUnknownMessagesRcvd.name: frextDlcmiLmiUnknownMessagesRcvd
frextDlcmiLmiUnknownMessagesRcvd.description: Number of Unknown LMI messages received on this interface.

frextDlcmiLmiStatusLostSequences.name: frextDlcmiLmiStatusLostSequences
frextDlcmiLmiStatusLostSequences.description: The total number of times a loss of sequencing in received STATUS messages was detected on this interface.

frextDlcmiLmiStatusEnqLostSequences.name: frextDlcmiLmiStatusEnqLostSequences
frextDlcmiLmiStatusEnqLostSequences.description: The total number of times a loss of sequencing in received STATUS ENQUIRY messages was detected on this interface.

frextDlcmiLmiMissingStatEnquiries.name: frextDlcmiLmiMissingStatEnquiries
frextDlcmiLmiMissingStatEnquiries.description: The number of times an expected STATUS ENQUIRY message was not received within the expected time on this interface.

frextDlcmiLmiUnexpectedPVCStatMsg.name: frextDlcmiLmiUnexpectedPVCStatMsg
frextDlcmiLmiUnexpectedPVCStatMsg.description: The number of LMI messages that were received with unexpected PVC STATUS IE on this interface.

frextDlcmiLmiUnexpectedDLCI.name: frextDlcmiLmiUnexpectedDLCI
frextDlcmiLmiUnexpectedDLCI.description: The number of STATUS messages received with unconfigured DLCI

frextDlcmiLmiStatEnqRatePlus.name: frextDlcmiLmiStatEnqRatePlus
frextDlcmiLmiStatEnqRatePlus.description: The number of times the STATUS ENQUIRY message was received more frequently than expected. For STRATACOM only

frextDlcmiLmiInvInfoFrame.name: frextDlcmiLmiInvInfoFrame
frextDlcmiLmiInvInfoFrame.description: The number of times an LMI message was received with information type not equal to unnumbered information type.

frextDlcmiLmiInvFrameHdr.name: frextDlcmiLmiInvFrameHdr
frextDlcmiLmiInvFrameHdr.description: The number of LMI frames received with error in the header bits.

frextDlcmiLmiNoIERepType.name: frextDlcmiLmiNoIERepType
frextDlcmiLmiNoIERepType.description: The number of times an LMI frame was received with missing Report Type IE

frextDlcmiLmiNoIEKeepAlive.name: frextDlcmiLmiNoIEKeepAlive
frextDlcmiLmiNoIEKeepAlive.description: The number of times an LMI frame was received with missing Link Integrity Verification IE.

frextDlcmiLmiMissingResponses.name: frextDlcmiLmiMissingResponses
frextDlcmiLmiMissingResponses.description: The total number of times a timeout occurred without receiving a response to an LMI request by this interface.

frextDlcmiLmiUnsuppIERcvd.name: frextDlcmiLmiUnsuppIERcvd
frextDlcmiLmiUnsuppIERcvd.description: The number of LMI messages received with unknown Information Element.

frextDlcmiPvccs.name: frextDlcmiPvccs
frextDlcmiPvccs.description: The number of permanent VCCs established on this Frame Relay logical interface

frextCircuitTable.name: frextCircuitTable
frextCircuitTable.description: A table containing information about specific Data Link Connection Identifiers and corresponding connections.

frextCircuitEntry.name: frextCircuitEntry
frextCircuitEntry.description: The information regarding a single Data Link Connection Identifier.

frextCircuitServiceIfIndex.name: frextCircuitServiceIfIndex
frextCircuitServiceIfIndex.description: IfIndex of the Frame Relay Interface,UNI, to which data received from ATM is forwarded.The index generated by the agent for Frame Relay service identification. This index is volatile over power down

frextCircuitName.name: frextCircuitName
frextCircuitName.description: The user-defined name for the connection.

frextCircuitProfileFrRateIndex.name: frextCircuitProfileFrRateIndex
frextCircuitProfileFrRateIndex.description: Index of the ProfileFRRateTable (rate enforcement/rate adaptation configuration for this FR/ATM interworking connection

frextCircuitREMonitor.name: frextCircuitREMonitor
frextCircuitREMonitor.description: This object enables or disables the monitoring of Bc, Be and CIR on the Rx side of the connection, called Rate Enforcement.If set to none, no monitoring will be performed. If set to standard, Rx monitoring will drop any frames received in excess of Be, and will tag frames received in between Bc and Be

frextCircuitRateFallbacks.name: frextCircuitRateFallbacks
frextCircuitRateFallbacks.description: The number of times that the insertion rate was lowered (due to network congestion reports) since the connection was created.

frextCircuitRateFallforwards.name: frextCircuitRateFallforwards
frextCircuitRateFallforwards.description: The number of times that the insertion rate was increased (due to lack of network congestion reports) since the connection was created.

frextCircuitEgFramesDroppedQueueFull.name: frextCircuitEgFramesDroppedQueueFull
frextCircuitEgFramesDroppedQueueFull.description: Number of frames which were dropped on this connection because the hold queue was full.

frextCircuitNormalSentFrames.name: frextCircuitNormalSentFrames
frextCircuitNormalSentFrames.description: Number of frames sent on this connection within the Commited Information Rate since the connection was created.

frextCircuitNormalSentOctets.name: frextCircuitNormalSentOctets
frextCircuitNormalSentOctets.description: Number of octets sent on this connection within the Commited Information Rate since the connection was created.

frextCircuitExcessSentOctets.name: frextCircuitExcessSentOctets
frextCircuitExcessSentOctets.description: Number of octets sent on this connection above the Commited Information Rate, but below the Excess Information Rate since the connection was created.

frextCircuitHeldBuffers.name: frextCircuitHeldBuffers
frextCircuitHeldBuffers.description: Number of buffers which were used by the connection for enqueueing frames in preference to exceeding the allowed burst rate on this connection since the connection was created.

frextCircuitOctetsOnQueue.name: frextCircuitOctetsOnQueue
frextCircuitOctetsOnQueue.description: Number of octets currently being used for enqueueing frames in order to be transmited.

frextCircuitBuffersOnQueue.name: frextCircuitBuffersOnQueue
frextCircuitBuffersOnQueue.description: Number of buffers currently being used for enqueueing frames in order to be transmited.

frextCircuitRxMonNormalFrames.name: frextCircuitRxMonNormalFrames
frextCircuitRxMonNormalFrames.description: The number of frames received on the connection within the committed burst (Bc).

frextCircuitRxMonNormalOctets.name: frextCircuitRxMonNormalOctets
frextCircuitRxMonNormalOctets.description: The number of octets received on the connection within the committed burst (Bc).

frextCircuitRxMonExcessOctets.name: frextCircuitRxMonExcessOctets
frextCircuitRxMonExcessOctets.description: The number of octets received on the connection within the excess burst (Be).

frextCircuitRxMonDroppedOctets.name: frextCircuitRxMonDroppedOctets
frextCircuitRxMonDroppedOctets.description: The number of octets received on the connection that were dropped because they were in excess Bc+Be.

frextCircuitRxMonDroppedDEFrames.name: frextCircuitRxMonDroppedDEFrames
frextCircuitRxMonDroppedDEFrames.description: The number of frames with the DE bit set received on the connection that were dropped.

frextCircuitRxMonDroppedDEOctets.name: frextCircuitRxMonDroppedDEOctets
frextCircuitRxMonDroppedDEOctets.description: The number of octets in frames with the DE bit set received on the connection that were dropped.

frextCircuitRxMonDEOctets.name: frextCircuitRxMonDEOctets
frextCircuitRxMonDEOctets.description: The number of octets with the DE bit set that were received on the connection.

frextCircuitRxMonSetDEFrames.name: frextCircuitRxMonSetDEFrames
frextCircuitRxMonSetDEFrames.description: The number of frames received on the connection in which the Rx monitor set the DE bit.

frextCircuitRxMonSetDEOctets.name: frextCircuitRxMonSetDEOctets
frextCircuitRxMonSetDEOctets.description: The number of octets in frames received on the connection in which the Rx monitor set the DE bit.

frextCircuitRecvdBECNS.name: frextCircuitRecvdBECNS
frextCircuitRecvdBECNS.description: Number of frames received from the network in- dicating forward congestion since the connection was created. This object is defined in this table to provide the same object as defined in RFC 1315, while the interface is defined as a DCE.

frextCircuitRecvdFECNS.name: frextCircuitRecvdFECNS
frextCircuitRecvdFECNS.description: Number of frames received from the network in- dicating backward congestion since the connection was created.This object is defined in this table to provide the same object as defined in RFC 1315, while the interface is defined as a DCE.

frsOamF5AtmVci.description: VCI of the ATM VCC on which FR DLCI maps onto

frsOamF5AISRxCounter.description: Number of VC-AIS cells received since the PVC was brought into service.

frsOamF5RDIRxCounter.name: frsOamF5RDIRxCounter
frsOamF5RDIRxCounter.description: Number of VC-RDI cells received since the PVC was brought into service.

frsOamF5RDITxCounter.name: frsOamF5RDITxCounter
frsOamF5RDITxCounter.description: Number of VC-RDI cells transmited since the PVC was brought into service.
